Package: EJAM
Type: Package
Title: Environmental Justice Analysis Multisite tool
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Original version of code to find nearby blocks was by Andreas Maier, Abt Associates March 2016,
    extensively modified by EPA (Johnathan Tafoya, Mark Corrales, and others) in 2021
Maintainer: The package maintainer <corrales.mark@epa.gov>
Description: Tools for summarizing environmental and demographic indicators (such as those in EJSCREEN)
    for residents living near any one of a number of specific sites. 
    It uses quad tree search/indexing of block locations, data.table, parallel processing 
    to provide very fast identification of nearby blocks, distances, and 
    aggregation of indicators within each distance.
    It can be uses as a web app, with the user interface provided by the shiny R package.
Requires: foreach, blockdata, frsdata
Imports: data.table, DBI, RMySQL, SearchTrees, doSNOW,
        sp, pdist
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
NeedsCompilation: no
Packaged: 2021-10-04 15:04:17 UTC; markcorrales
